Author: jameskbh
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Quote from: jameskbh on June 21, 2017, 10:53:06 AM Quote from: jameskbh on June 20, 2017, 10:48:39 AM Hello Sylon  I sent another PM to you today! Can you check it? Thanks! @Sylon I believe that you didn't see this last post or the PMs that I sent to you. Can you check it please? Thanks!  ____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________  As I got no answer in PMs here and in slack channel, I'm posting this in the thread to see if I get, at least, an answer better than the first one.  In June 19th I sent this message:  Hello!  I take a look at the spreadsheet and noticed that my translation was erased from it. It was the last one to receive the 116 stakes for the translation, and now the arabian one is showing in this last spot. It was not made using Google Translator, and I'm wondering why this happen. Can you tell my what drove this decision?  https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzeYkYQ_M1dTYXlfSTlnSmhKNjQ/view?usp=sharing  PT-BR PrimalbaseWP.pdf - Google Drive drive.google.com  _______________________________________________________________________________ _______________________ I got this answer:  1) You used Google translate. 2) What is that account ? Seriously ?  Next time, be smarter.  __________________________________________________________________________________________________________ After that, I replied:  Sylon,  1) I understand that you obviously have a lot on your mind, but I DO NOT use google translator. I'm really trying to talk to you to try to work this out. Can you point me what made you think that this translation was made using GTranslator?  I work with translations for a long time and also produce content about cryptocurrencies for at least 2 years.  2) I quite didn't understand this point. That's because my account has almost no posts? I use BTCTalk mostly for reading and to update myself about the market. If you take a closer look, will see that my account is from March 2015.  I'm not trying to fool you or harm the Primalbase project. I hope that we can continue this conversation to solve this issue that, in my point of view, a mistake. Can you take these arguments into consideration? _______________________________________________________________________________ _______________________ Followed by this one:  Hello Sylon,  In my last attempt to show you that I did not use Google Translator to do my work, I paste here the fisrt page of my translation and the GTranslator, to you compare:  G Translator:  Primalbase: espaço de trabalho distribuído para Tech Comunidade Amesterdão, maio de 2017 Primal@primalbase.com Www.primalbase.com Abstrato. Com base no negócio bem estabelecido Modelo de espaços de trabalho compartilhados, o projeto Primalbase Transforma o aluguel de escritório tradicional em uma nova geração Ecossistema baseado na comunidade, onde se pode compartilhar, vender ou Alugue espaços de escritório de alta qualidade usando Ethereum e Tokens digitais baseados em ondas. Totais primários não só Servem uma função prática, mas também têm inerente Valor baseado em um produto físico real: é isso que faz Primalbase se destaca de outros projetos utilizando cripto Tokens. A concepção do projeto e seus elementos centrais São delineados neste artigo. 1. Introdução O setor imobiliário é uma das áreas mais conservadoras da economia, enquanto Blockchain é considerada uma tecnologia inovadora e disruptiva. Mesmo assim, A combinação desses elementos aparentemente incompatíveis provou ser extremamente frutífera - um exemplo saliente de WeWork. A base da maioria dos projetos cooperativos é o conceito de criar um compartilhamento Infra-estrutura com uma comunidade global. As vantagens desse modelo comercial Sobre as práticas de gestão de grandes corporações, com sua rígida interna Regulamentos e hierarquia rígida, são bastante evidentes. Isto é especialmente verdadeiro para Novas empresas tecnológicas, que rejeitam cada vez mais o tradicional Escritório configurado em favor de ambientes de trabalho. Este formato ganhou muito Tração: de acordo com a Pesquisa Global de Coworking 2017, o número de novos Os projetos de coworking duplicaram praticamente desde 2011, e o número de seus Os residentes são estimados em 1,2 milhões (veja também o fig. 1).   My translation:  Primalbase: Espaço de Trabalho Distribuído para a Comunidade Tecnológica Amsterdã, maio de 2017 primal@primalbase.com www.primalbase.com Resumo. Com base em modelos de negócio bem estabelecido de espaços de trabalho compartilhados, o projeto Primalbase transforma o aluguel de escritórios tradicionais em um ecossistema comunitário de nova geração, onde se pode compartilhar, vender ou alugar espaços de escritórios de alta qualidade usando tokens digitais baseados em Ethereum e Waves. Os tokens da Primalbase não tem apenas uma função prática, mas também têm um valor inerente real, com base em um produto físico real: é isso que faz com que a Primalbase se destaque de outros projetos que utilizam tokens de criptografia. A concepção do projeto e seus elementos principais são delineados neste artigo. 1. Introdução O setor imobiliário é uma das áreas mais conservadoras da economia, enquanto o Blockchain é considerado uma tecnologia inovadora e disruptiva. No entanto, combinar esses elementos aparentemente incompatíveis provou ser extremamente frutífero - um exemplo importante sendo o WeWork. A base da maioria dos projetos de colaboração é o conceito de criar uma infraestrutura compartilhada com uma comunidade global. As vantagens deste modelo de negócios sobre as práticas de gestão das grandes corporações, com seus regulamentos internos rígidos e hierarquia engessada, são bastante evidentes. Isto é especialmente verdadeiro para as novas startups tecnológicas, que rejeitam cada vez mais o escritório tradicional, em favor de ambientes de colaboração. Este formato ganhou muita força: de acordo com a 2017 Global Coworking Survey, o número de novos projetos de coworking dobrou aproximadamente desde 2011, e o número de utilizadores é estimado em 1,2 milhões (ver também figura 1).   As anyone can see, the translations are quite different. Fell free to download it from gdrive!  Maybe now can I get an answer?

Body: Primalbase - a rare case of Blockchain implementation in real economy. Creating a high-quality infrastructure for small-team projects, Primalbase is set to disrupt Real Estate industry by building a strong community of entrepreneurs, developers, investors; by offering them a groundbreaking financial tool - PBT tokens that can be rented out, traded or used to access any Primalbase office in tech hubs around the world.

Author: danielj314
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Well, I think you'd have to assume they've updated the website to reflect the current advisors and supporters. Vitalik obviously made a very public announcement that he is stepping away from formal endorsements of any projects and the website has been adjusted accordingly. Sasha Ivanov, the founder of Waves, made a public statement at the same time emphasizing that he will still vouch for a few projects only if and when he fully believes in them. So his continued endorsement is very meaningful given the fact that Primal Base will be so solidly built on Waves tech.  I think all these questions are totally legitimate to ask. I'd recommend that Dmitry put out another edition of his Q and A series and take on these two questions first and second. The one about who he intends to have on his marketing, legal, etc team and what is the current status of advisors?  I'm guessing he has satisfying answers to both.

Author: danielj314
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: From where I sit it appears Dmitry has everything he needs to bring this project to pass successfully. The most compelling evidence is the fact that a Proof of Concept office is up and running in Amsterdam. I don't know the make up of the group who have helped Dmitry make that happen, but I trust that it can be replicated again and again.  Also there are more than a "couple" advisors listed and all of them are heavyweights. I recently heard Sasha Ivanov, the founder of Waves, say that he would not lend his name as an advisor to a project unless he could strongly vouch for their trustworthiness. I'm sure he has evaluated the full scale and scope of this project. Given the information he has access to, I would trust his ability to spot red flags a lot more than someone reading posts on Bitcointalk.  Finally, I see nothing at all unusual about the kind of posts made in this thread. It's all very typical stuff for any project in an ICO phase. Sure, there are a lot of silly posts from people trying to meet quotas. But that happens with all projects and campaigns and is hardly indicative of the overall strength of the project.

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: The foundation of most co-working projects is the concept of creating a shared infrastructure with a global community. The advantages of this business model over the management practices of large corporations, with their rigid internal regulations and strict hierarchy, are quite apparent. This is especially true for young technological start-ups, who are increasingly rejecting the traditional office set up in favour of co-working environments. This format has gained much traction: according to 2017 Global Coworking Survey, the number of new coworking projects has roughly doubled since 2011, and the number of their residents is estimated at 1.2 million

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Quote from: vindyne8 on June 09, 2017, 04:08:12 PM   Primalbase ICO starts on June, 26 2017! This is your chance to invest in a tangible product developed by an all-star team matching real and crypto economies. Don’t miss it - 66% bonus for early investors. Learn more at http://primalbase.com   Interview: Vitalik Buterin on Scaling Ethereum, Its Popularity in Asia and ICOs https://bitcoinmagazine.com/articles/interview-vitalik-buterin-ethereum-scaling-issues-popularity-asia-and-icos/   Buterin was recently appointed as an advisor to the board of Primalbase, a startup that is aiming to tokenize a WeWork or Regus-type co-working space provider and grant micro-ownership to its investors.   “I’m definitely very interested in all these applications, particularly the semi-financial ones with some components of finance and monetary value but also some components outside of it” said Buterin. “The general idea that we can create this economy where we micro-tokenize and let people have their own micro-ownership, I think that is definitely a very interesting and promising idea.”       Sasha Ivanov, CEO of Waves in CoinTelegraph Article:  https://cointelegraph.com/news/we-are-witnessing-brilliant-example-of-crowd-intelligence-sasha-ivanov-on-icos  Quote “Primalbase is a real estate project, while it is also a Blockchain community project. It offers a rather unique product - on the one hand, it is an access to co-working, on the other hand, it is a financial instrument, which can be traded on the market. There hasn’t been anything like this before. It can unite many startups within the community. Many cryptocurrency startups are getting interested in sharing Primalbase co-working spaces, soon we might see the development of a new environment for cryptocurrency businesses, that will go out of the virtual world into the real one, in particular, geographical locations, it will be interesting.”  Ivanov notes:  Quote “Integration of tokens into this model allows for greater simplicity and transparency. You can, of course, agree with a person without a token but with a token, it is easier. This is going to be the very first project which will be pushing leasing of financial instruments through Blockchain, it is a very interesting scheme.”  Ivanov thinks that the Primalbase project is going to demonstrate a fast expansion, triggering the development of a new business ecosystem and creation of a new economy.   Quote from: sasha35625 on June 10, 2017, 12:32:41 PM yes, I fully support this project, the idea of this project was born while discussing issues in the existing model of co-working industry with Dmitry. As for Vitalik - Dimtry talked to him while he was in Moscow, and Vitalik liked the idea. I'm an advisor to the project and we'll use Primalbase office space.

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: The Amsterdam office is at Helicopterstraat 25, 1059CE Amsterdam. You can tour the location in person if you call ahead here: +31 6 58723044  You can see lots of pictures and a couple videos of the space and some of it's occupants here:  https://www.instagram.com/primalbase https://www.facebook.com/primalbasehq  As for the value proposition, it is not just a workspace. It is also a token that is a store of value, sellable, and leasable, and is also tradable on exchanges. It is up to the individual if they find that more appealing than a standard monthly rent payment or not.

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Quote from: vindyne8 on June 09, 2017, 04:08:12 PM    Primalbase ICO starts on June, 26 2017! This is your chance to invest in a tangible product developed by an all-star team matching real and crypto economies. Don’t miss it - 66% bonus for early investors. Learn more at http://primalbase.com   Interview: Vitalik Buterin on Scaling Ethereum, Its Popularity in Asia and ICOs https://bitcoinmagazine.com/articles/interview-vitalik-buterin-ethereum-scaling-issues-popularity-asia-and-icos/    Buterin was recently appointed as an advisor to the board of Primalbase, a startup that is aiming to tokenize a WeWork or Regus-type co-working space provider and grant micro-ownership to its investors.   “I’m definitely very interested in all these applications, particularly the semi-financial ones with some components of finance and monetary value but also some components outside of it” said Buterin. “The general idea that we can create this economy where we micro-tokenize and let people have their own micro-ownership, I think that is definitely a very interesting and promising idea.”       Sasha Ivanov, CEO of Waves in CoinTelegraph Article:  https://cointelegraph.com/news/we-are-witnessing-brilliant-example-of-crowd-intelligence-sasha-ivanov-on-icos  Quote “Primalbase is a real estate project, while it is also a Blockchain community project. It offers a rather unique product - on the one hand, it is an access to co-working, on the other hand, it is a financial instrument, which can be traded on the market. There hasn’t been anything like this before. It can unite many startups within the community. Many cryptocurrency startups are getting interested in sharing Primalbase co-working spaces, soon we might see the development of a new environment for cryptocurrency businesses, that will go out of the virtual world into the real one, in particular, geographical locations, it will be interesting.”  Ivanov notes:  Quote “Integration of tokens into this model allows for greater simplicity and transparency. You can, of course, agree with a person without a token but with a token, it is easier. This is going to be the very first project which will be pushing leasing of financial instruments through Blockchain, it is a very interesting scheme.”  Ivanov thinks that the Primalbase project is going to demonstrate a fast expansion, triggering the development of a new business ecosystem and creation of a new economy.   Quote from: sasha35625 on June 10, 2017, 12:32:41 PM yes, I fully support this project, the idea of this project was born while discussing issues in the existing model of co-working industry with Dmitry. As for Vitalik - Dimtry talked to him while he was in Moscow, and Vitalik liked the idea. I'm an advisor to the project and we'll use Primalbase office space.

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Quote from: vindyne8 on June 09, 2017, 04:08:12 PM   Primalbase ICO starts on June, 26 2017! This is your chance to invest in a tangible product developed by an all-star team matching real and crypto economies. Don’t miss it - 66% bonus for early investors. Learn more at http://primalbase.com   Interview: Vitalik Buterin on Scaling Ethereum, Its Popularity in Asia and ICOs https://bitcoinmagazine.com/articles/interview-vitalik-buterin-ethereum-scaling-issues-popularity-asia-and-icos/    Buterin was recently appointed as an advisor to the board of Primalbase, a startup that is aiming to tokenize a WeWork or Regus-type co-working space provider and grant micro-ownership to its investors.   “I’m definitely very interested in all these applications, particularly the semi-financial ones with some components of finance and monetary value but also some components outside of it” said Buterin. “The general idea that we can create this economy where we micro-tokenize and let people have their own micro-ownership, I think that is definitely a very interesting and promising idea.”       Sasha Ivanov, CEO of Waves in CoinTelegraph Article:  https://cointelegraph.com/news/we-are-witnessing-brilliant-example-of-crowd-intelligence-sasha-ivanov-on-icos  Quote “Primalbase is a real estate project, while it is also a Blockchain community project. It offers a rather unique product - on the one hand, it is an access to co-working, on the other hand, it is a financial instrument, which can be traded on the market. There hasn’t been anything like this before. It can unite many startups within the community. Many cryptocurrency startups are getting interested in sharing Primalbase co-working spaces, soon we might see the development of a new environment for cryptocurrency businesses, that will go out of the virtual world into the real one, in particular, geographical locations, it will be interesting.”  Ivanov notes:  Quote “Integration of tokens into this model allows for greater simplicity and transparency. You can, of course, agree with a person without a token but with a token, it is easier. This is going to be the very first project which will be pushing leasing of financial instruments through Blockchain, it is a very interesting scheme.”  Ivanov thinks that the Primalbase project is going to demonstrate a fast expansion, triggering the development of a new business ecosystem and creation of a new economy.

Author: mdkb
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: but the 'team'on the website isnt the actual team at all, they are using key players in crypto who have maybe expressed interest at best, or joined the community. whoever is behind this is then making it look like they are the devs, but they are not. what does ''advisor'' mean exactly? it can mean nothing.  in fact so far there seems to be no mention on the web site who the actual people behind this are, who are the devs and who is behind this, the planners. is it Dimtry Faller alone?  it seems like a great idea and yet there are some huge gaps in it becoming a reality; like the price of the coin being insanely high, and then the total investment from the ICO wont end up being enough to buy the real estate they say they are looking at.  also is there any real proof that the photos of Amsterdam are not just staged photoshoot with people and props in a rental? anyone confirmed this is real anywhere yet?  I would like to see the actual dev team, the real people behind this, and not just photos of Sasha Ivanov and Vitalik Buterin listed as advisors.  They are NOT the team, they are just advisors, which basically means they could have had their emails added to the community forum, and said a few nice words, nothing more.   EDIT:  ok quick check and I found Sasha is actually promoting this as a 'big ICO coming up' on his twitter feed but be aware he is probably getting paid for that. and his actual involvment is nothing more than to have signed up to the community and agreed to be listed as an advisor, I dont see his involvement being much beyond the fact someone is using Waves to create an ICO, so it suits his business in that regard.  be very wary until the actual devs reveal themselves and stop using the coattails of Sasha and Vitalik to promote this ICO.

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: We appreciate your feedback, but this project differs in one respect from almost all others, each of our tokens represents a physical thing in the real world.   Quote from: bennyparker on June 09, 2017, 11:40:42 AM Quote from: The Goat Master on June 09, 2017, 11:33:57 AM Quote from: bennyparker on June 09, 2017, 11:31:19 AM So two thing I'm kinda eager to know is:  1. How much space does 1 token grant you? 2. For how long are you able to use the space that the 1 token grants you? - e.g. can you only use the space 1 month in a whole year? Or is the space actually yours for ever for 1 token?   As I understand: 1. 1 PBT means 1 membership. 2. Lifetime  So to be clear, 1 membership is 1 person and 1 seat yes ?   From the whitepaper section 3.2:  Quote 3.2 Token specification   One PBT token allows full access to the shared workspace at any Primalbase location for one person. In every office space, all the necessary services and amenities will be present and provided, such as broadband Internet access, digital printing, etc. The term of the token is unlimited and, therefore, does not expire. The fee itself is secured in a single payment. The number of tokens that can be purchased by the same holder is unlimited. In this case, the possession of 4 tokens permits the use of a private office, if one is available.   Read more:  http://primalbase.com/assets/PrimalbaseWP.pdf

Author: ManagerVirta
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Probably because of the availability of a real product. In addition, the deficit will positively affect speculation. Part of the answer is here: https://medium.com/@primalbase/q-a-1-primalbase-ico-83dbaa0f88e5 Quote 7. “Why so few coins, people won’t like owning 0.0001 of a token” It is a matter of denomination. Why pumping up an artificial value? 1 token equals to 1 membership spot. Why are we creating splits? The reason lies in the fact that 1 token is not only one membership spot and access to the infrastructure, it is also a financial tool. What is the meaning of crowdfunding campaign? Everyone has a chance to buy in even with a small account of stakes, and nevertheless be directly involved into development of the project. The entry threshold for buying into our project is significantly reduced. We don’t intend to create anything extra, if it is not needed. Let’s say creating 10 000 tokens. I don’t understand what are the 10 000 tokens for — it is like having 10 000 keys. I need only one key, which opens all of the doors, I don’t need to have 10 000 of those. I have only one key which gives me access to all, it is my universal digital code. But in order to ensure a greater flexibility for people who would like to join our project, we decided to create a certain split of 0.0001. Bitcoin has 8 digits after decimal point, while Primalbase has only 4, there is an explanation behind it, I don’t see the point in having such a division.

Author: Gekko463
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: It fails the Howey test blatantly:  "We intend to create larger scale and all-encompassing hubs at the most suitable locations. A part of the profit made from these ventures will be distributed amongst token holders"  The tokens are profit participation "shares". Therefore the are securities which must be registered before being sold to unsophisticated investors.  OP even refers to them as "financial instruments" above.  It is completely pre-mined.  Completely centralized.  This could be the project where the SEC finally puts someone in jail for hawking unregistered  financial instruments to unsophisticated investors without a brokers licence.  Because these guys just don't give ANY fucks and believe themselves to be outside of the laws that apply to mere mortals.  Further, Co-working spaces keep failing where I live, in Hanoi.  I have seen a half dozen of them come and go in the last few years.  What the fuck is it?  A coffee shop where you have to pay for your seat, and then pay for your coffee?  I don't get why somebody would go to a co-working space when the cafe gives you the seat for free when you pay for your coffee.  This is a sign of the bubble bursting soon.

Author: digitalgrow
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Been waiting a few weeks for the details of this to be released, I love the concept and am interested in taking an office in your London location.  Could you please advise if the offices for the remaining 4 locations have been finalised or are you still searching for suitable premises? Procuring real estate can be a long process at times and it would be nice to know that you are able to meet the deadlines stated on obtaining your locations.  Where will your London offices be located? I would ideally like to know before investing for travel purposes  From what i can see you are aiming to raise between 3000 and 5000 btc. From current pricings this would be between 6 and 10 million, lets say 1.2-2 million per location. You would not be able to purchase any significant office space for this price in East London so I assume you will be leasing the locations? If this is the case how long are your lease agreements?  How many workspaces/offices there will be per location?  Will all token holder be guaranteed a workstation if they choose to use the location? The worst thing that could happen with this project is that token holders arrive to use their workspace and there are not enough for all token holders for that day. Lets say there is a crypto conference in London and investors want to use their token whilst they are there to do some work. What if maybe 100 token holders arrive and there are not enough workspaces? Or what if a location is oversubscribed after ICO and there will not be enough spaces?  Also I wanted to ask how are the offices? What is the size, layout, is it an closed office for privacy etc? Could you please post an example from your Amsterdam location so investors can see better what is the benefit of investing in an office over a workstation  If an investor was to invest in 4 tokens for the office, how long would the term be for? Would there be an legal contract provided as a proof of tenancy/lease agreement for investors?  I am keen to invest in this project as I know the concept is in use a lot here and there is many opportunity for this sector

Author: herromerro
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: I think this project is very good. This is great tokenize example of real world business.  But some doubts about the funding process.  You'll sell 1000 PBT Maybe you sell them all at the first day of ICO. And that means 3000BTC Maybe you sell them all 2-7 days of ICO. And that means 4000BTC Maybe you sell them all after seventh day of ICO. And that means 5000BTC  And maybe BTC price will be 1k or 5k.  Yes, my examples a bit unrealistic but my point is your funding process too volatile. How much Primal Base need for sustainable business model, for establish 4 other work spaces, expenses? The target shouldn't base on USD or some not volatile too much and convertible currency?  If you rent those places, pay all expenses with BTC, you're right. But otherwise I don't get it.

Author: Primal Base
Title: Primalbase - Distributed Workspace for Tech Community
Body: Book your workspace now with Primalbase token (PBT) or Ether (ETH)  for less than €2 per day in Berlin and Amsterdam!   Register now --> Primalbase Booking Platform      All our offices are located in the cities with thriving tech communities. Want to learn more? Check out Primalbase Website  ********  Latest news:  We've got an awesome range of events taking place across our spaces over the next couple of months, with everything from zero knowledge proofs courses to meetups on regulation in #AI, check it out! Hope to see you there https://primalbase.com/en/events/  FIRST LOOK - Primalbase hits the Big Apple! Presenting our new office space in  New York - opening soon. Who's ready to get down to business in this incredible city?    Reports: July 2017 - August 2017 - September 2017 - October 2017 - November 2017 - December 2017 - January 2018 - February 2018 - March 2018 - April 2018 - May 2018 - June 2018 - July 2018 -  August 2018 - September 2018 - October 2018 - November 2018 - Annual Report 2018 - January 2019 - February 2019 - March 2019 - April 2019 - May 2019  FAQ: Part 1 - Part 2 - Part 3 - Part 4 - Part 5 - Part 6 - Part 7 -  Media about Primalbase: Forbes Huffington Post Bitcoin Magazine The Cointelegraph Iamsterdam  Sprout Finance Magnates VC Sputnik Coinfox Philly Coinspeaker The Blockchain The Merkle  The Market Mogul Startup Valley Duitslandnieuws  ********  Our team  Primalbase is, at its heart, about developing a community and fostering collaboration - and this starts with our passionate team. We have an incredible team who work hard behind the scenes to make Primalbase what it is, and they are always on hand to support our community.   Advisory Board  Our Board consists of some of the most reputable advisors in the Blockchain industry   ********  Contacts  Contact the team on Slack and Telegram  Stay updated on our Social Media: Facebook Twitter Instagram   ********  Vitalik Buterin, Co-Founder at Ethereum:  “I’m definitely very interested in all these applications, particularly the semi-financial ones with some components of finance and monetary value but also some components outside of it. The general idea that we can create this economy where we micro-tokenize and let people have their own micro-ownership, I think that is definitely a very interesting and promising idea.”  Read more: https://bitcoinmagazine.com/articles/interview-vitalik-buterin-ethereum-scaling-issues-popularity-asia-and-icos/  Sasha Ivanov, CEO and Founder of the Waves Platform:  “Primalbase is a real estate project, while it is also a Blockchain community project. It offers a rather unique product - on the one hand, it is an access to co-working, on the other hand, it is a financial instrument, which can be traded on the market. There hasn’t been anything like this before. It can unite many startups within the community. Many cryptocurrency startups are getting interested in sharing Primalbase co-working spaces, soon we might see the development of a new environment for cryptocurrency businesses, that will go out of the virtual world into the real one, in particular, geographical locations, it will be interesting.”  Read more: https://cointelegraph.com/news/we-are-witnessing-brilliant-example-of-crowd-intelligence-sasha-ivanov-on-icos   Dmitry Faller, Researcher, Founder of Blockchain Institute:  “We have been seriously involved in the Blockchain industry for a few years and found it interesting to try to implement this technology in the commercial real estate industry, to give a technology access to the physical environment. We started thinking about how to build a digital analog for community membership mechanisms and we believe that this is one of the cases where Blockchain technology is indeed useful.”  Read more: https://cointelegraph.com/news/sharing-economy-why-blockchain-might-be-next-big-thing-for-office-rental  Dmitry Tokarev, Chief Technology Officer of Dolfin:  “At Dolfin we also provide a service to all sorts of clients from all over the world and it seems like such a great idea to have a place where you are guaranteed to have a productive time whilst on a business trip and the same level of service wherever you are.”  Read more: http://themarketmogul.com/coworking-spaces-office-rental/  Billy Draper, VC, Partner at Draper Associates:  “That’s cool, they found a real world application, and that’s what we want to see - we don’t want to see more coins in the world. That is a game-changing thinking, the same with real estate. Renting out these tokens? That is how you start the real revolution, that’s how things will go from Bitcoin sort of still crypto community which is getting bigger.”  Read more: https://cointelegraph.com/news/billy-drapers-investment-tips-cryptocurrencies-icos-bubbles-ct-exclusive   ********   IN OTHER LANGUAGES  FRENCH - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ  SPANISH - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ 1 FAQ 2 FAQ 4 FAQ 5  ITALIAN - Main Thread  DUTCH - Main Thread  GERMAN - Main Thread  PORTUGUESE - Main Thread  CHINESE - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ  FILIPINO - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ  MALAYSIAN - Main Thread  HINDI - Main Thread  TAMIL - Main Thread  RUSSIAN - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ 1 FAQ 2  UKRAINIAN - Main Thread FAQ  SERBIAN - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ  HUNGARIAN - Main Thread  SLOVENIAN - Main Thread  CROATIAN - Main Thread Whitepaper  BULGARIAN - Whitepaper  TURKISH - Main Thread Whitepaper FAQ  ARABIC - Whitepaper
